  "observation": "Brainstorm triggered by plateau. 4 proposals generated.",
  "suggestion": "The plateau occurs because the system has optimized organisms as isolated agents in a static, homogeneous environment. Selection pressure has thinned—there are no new niches, no new interaction modes, no new phenotypic dimensions worth exploring. The evolutionary algorithm is exhausted *not because organisms are perfect, but because the environment offers no reason to be different.* Adding structure (sensory diversity, temporal phases, social communication) doesn't just tune parameters—it redefines which organisms can exist and what 'success' means. The system needs ecosystem dynamics, not organism optimization.; [medium] Introduce multi-sensory systems and behavioral specialization. Add directional chemoreceptors, light-intensity sensors, and organism-type detectors (not just collision). Organisms develop distinct behavioral archetypes: hunters, builders, grazers, scouts. Decision function now routes sensory input through specialized behavior modules. — Current organisms likely converged on identical collision-avoidance strategies. Adding sensory diversity opens a new strategy space: role-based specialization, coordinated group behavior, predator-prey arms races. Population stratification enables aesthetic dynamics (formations, synchronized movement, coordinated coloring) that single-strategy swarms cannot produce. Breaks plateau by rewarding behavioral complexity.; [hard] Implement developmental metamorphosis: organisms have distinct growth phases (larval, juvenile, adult) with different morphologies, movement speeds, and energy costs per phase. Transition timing is evolvable. Organisms can 'settle' into different final forms based on local conditions. — Static body design space is exhausted—organisms cannot improve by changing shape alone. Metamorphosis adds time-dimension to morphology: small-fast-expendable larvae + large-efficient-stable adults unlock new survival strategies (dispersal vs. settlement, energy timing, predation stages). Creates new beauty dimension: transformation elegance. Escapes current local optimum.; [medium] Add pheromone/signal emission and reception. Organisms can release chemical markers (evolvable signal type and intensity) and sense others' signals at distance. Signals persist briefly, diffuse, and influence behavior. Enable collective signaling: alarm, aggregation, reproduction attraction. — Breaks the 'each organism is independent' assumption. Enables emergent phenomena: swarming formations, cooperative defense, synchronized reproduction cycles. Beauty emerges from collective behavior (coordinated coloring responses, formation patterns) rather than individual morphology. Creates new social selection pressures that individual-only strategies cannot survive, forcing ecosystem rethinking. Fitness suddenly rewards group-level properties.",
